item.title: Mysevrer!please help for co-owner!
item.dc:creator: @old_nite old_nite
item.description:
@old_nite wrote:

better yet go to ur “start” button…then click on “run” then type “cmd”…when a black box comes up type in ipconfig/all at the end and hit enter… then it show show all the numbers and stuff…write down ur deffault gateway address and you I.P adress. then open internet explorer or whatever web browser u have and type in you gateway address in the address bar… it shuld come up and ask you for user name and password…the deffault name is “admin” and deffault password it “admin” or “password”… try that and then it shuld bring up some site if u typed the pass correctly, find the thing that says “portfowarding” it may also say "portfowarding/ port triggering…click on that and then youll see another page…click “add service”…you will now see another page asking for service name…enter something like mopar1…then for the service type make it TCP/UDP. for port # enter 43594 or ur servers port number (43594 is deffault unless you changed it). Then enter it again in second box. and for where it says ip address enter YOUR ip address, not the gateway address the ip address that i told you to write down along with gateway address…then click apply and there yo have it
